getName

public java.lang.String getName()
Description copied from interface: Contact
Returns the name of the contact. Note that some contactImporters cannot retrieve the name: in that case the name may be "" or even the empty string. Use getGeneratedName() if you realy need a name. A name is generated if none found.

Specified by:
getName in interface Contact

getGeneratedName

public java.lang.String getGeneratedName()
Description copied from interface: Contact
Returns the name of the contact. Or it generated a name from the email address if no name was found. Use this method if you really need a name but you are not sure if the contact has a name. Note that there is no guarantee that the name is unique.

Specified by:
getGeneratedName in interface Contact
Returns:
a string that can be used as the name for this contact
